*DefaultJiraDataImporter* class reads the values as follows

{code}
CustomFieldType customFieldType = customField.getCustomFieldType();
if (customFieldType instanceof MultiSelectCFType)
{
    valueToAdd = MultiSelectCFType.extractTransferObjectFromString(value);
}
else
{
    valueToAdd = customFieldType.getSingularObjectFromString(value);
}
{code}

however by definition in *system-customfields-plugin.xml* file

{code:xml}
<customfield-type key="multiversion" name="Version Picker" 
    ...
    class="com.atlassian.jira.issue.customfields.impl.VersionCFType">
    <param name="multiple" value="true" />
...
</customfield-type>

<customfield-type key="version" name="Single Version Picker"
    ...
    class="com.atlassian.jira.issue.customfields.impl.VersionCFType">
    <param name="multiple" value="false"/>
...
</customfield-type>
{code}

single value and multiple value version custom fields share the same implementation class ({{com.atlassian.jira.issue.customfields.impl.VersionCFType}}). This class does not implement {{MultiSelectCFType}} therefore cannot import multiple values.

