Mylyn (previously known as Mylar) is a great plugin for Eclipse that provides a task-focused workflow.

Starting with Eclipse 3.3, it is packaged with the Eclipse distributions.  Unfortunately, the JIRA connector for Mylyn is not, and has to be downloaded separately from an Eclipse update site that is not in the set of preconfigured update sites.  It is the only available connector that is labelled as having "Incubator" status, indicating that it lacks the level of quality of the other connectors available.

I'm trying to run the JIRA connector for Mylyn against jira.atlassian.com (3.10-DEV-190607-#251), but it doesn't seem to be retrieving filter results.

